ted checker—I've verified the source has exactly one h1 and eight h2 headings, matching the nine knowledge sections perfectly. Reviewing the s4 content more closely, I notice the knowledge version seems to cut off mid-sentence compared to the source, so I should verify that's been captured completely. The wording shift from the passive form to the active form is quite subtle—both convey essentially the same meaning about availability for large-scale systems, so this feels more like a minor grammatical variation than a substantive fabrication. I'll hold off on reporting this one since the core meaning remains intact.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16227,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16227,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9775257-8127-445a-85d9-f6d2425c5af0","uuid":"1d495e2a-1222-41c4-b2c5-9b5106ed1115"}
